author: julianfoad
msg: In the tests for merging a file deletion, add a sub-test for where the file
is the same only because of local mods, and make a few non-functional tweaks.
* subversion/tests/cmdline/merge_tests.py
(svn_mkfile): Don't set an extra property: there's no benefit.
(svn_modfile): New helper function.
(del_identical_file): Also test where file is the same due to local mods.
(del_sched_add_hist_file): Do the source set-up separately. Commit only
the source or target of interest, to make the verbose output easier to
follow where an earlier sub-test left something uncommitted.

author: julianfoad
msg: Update the tests for merge deleting a file. Extend to test for property
differences. Use greek-tree paths as much as possible. Simplify a bit.
A follow-up to r32405.
* subversion/tests/cmdline/merge_tests.py
(local_path): New helper function. Use it in the other helper functions
to make them accept slash-separated paths on all platforms, for
simplicity in the callers. Update the callers.
(svn_mkdir): Remove, as no longer used.
(svn_mkfile): Remove redundant text and commented-out code.
(svn_copy): Extend to take a source-revision argument. Update the callers.
(del_differing_file): Extend to also test property mods.
